{
  "texts": [
    "These models iteratively transform raw input features into more meaningful representations, enhancing predictive accuracy.",
    "Recent AI applications in aging biomarker studies DL in biomarker of aging developmentBiomarkers of aging are quantitative parameters measured in an organism to estimate biological age [55].",
    "They may also reflect mortality risk, frailty, and other age-associated conditions.",
    "There are three fundamental categories of biomarkers of aging: molecular (multi-omics, or other laboratory parameters), physiological (measured by functional performance) and digital (obtained through digital devices) [55].",
    "To support their development and validation, biomarker consortiums have been established in the United States [55] and China [56]."
  ]
}